‚ÄúI like to bottle up auras only I can see, in the hopes other people can see them too,‚Äù says Nat ƒÜmiel, the visual artist and musician who is manifesting the otherworldly, ethereal enigma that is yeule (@yeule).

‚ÄúThe yeule project is a sonic and visual time capsule that snapshots eras of my shape-shifting self and the experience of pathos. I want to hit that spot where it hurts so bad and burns so hot, but you can never take a picture or show anyone what it looked like. I won‚Äôt sing something I don‚Äôt mean, and I don‚Äôt play something I don‚Äôt really like. There must be a reason why I chip at this concrete so meticulously, right?
